%% Platform Data Flow Diagram - Red Hat OpenShift AI (RHOAI) 2.19
%% Generated by Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard<br/>8443/TCP oauth-proxy
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Pattern 1: KServe Serverless Model Serving
    participant IstioGW as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.3
    participant KnAct as Knative Activator<br/>mTLS
    participant KServePod as KServe Pod<br/>vLLM/TGIS/OVMS/Caikit
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    User->>Route: POST /v1/models/model:predict
    Route->>IstioGW: TLS Passthrough
    IstioGW->>KnAct: mTLS (Istio STRICT)
    KnAct->>KServePod: HTTP/8080 mTLS
    KServePod->>S3: Load Model Weights (HTTPS/443)
    S3-->>KServePod: Model Artifacts
    KServePod-->>KnAct: Inference Response
    KnAct-->>IstioGW: Response
    IstioGW-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: JSON Prediction

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Pattern 2: ModelMesh Multi-Model Serving
    participant MMPod as ModelMesh Pod<br/>Headless Service
    participant MMSidecar as modelmesh Sidecar<br/>gRPC/8033
    participant RestProxySC as rest-proxy Sidecar<br/>HTTP/8008
    participant RuntimeAdapterSC as runtime-adapter<br/>gRPC/8085
    participant etcd as etcd<br/>gRPC/2379

    User->>Route: POST /v2/models/model/infer
    Route->>RestProxySC: HTTPS Passthrough
    RestProxySC->>MMSidecar: REST-to-gRPC translation
    MMSidecar->>etcd: Model placement lookup
    etcd-->>MMSidecar: Model location
    MMSidecar->>RuntimeAdapterSC: Load model if needed
    RuntimeAdapterSC->>S3: Pull model weights
    S3-->>RuntimeAdapterSC: Model artifacts
    RuntimeAdapterSC-->>MMSidecar: Model loaded
    MMSidecar-->>RestProxySC: Inference result
    RestProxySC-->>Route: JSON Response
    Route-->>User: Prediction

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Pattern 3: Data Science Pipeline Execution
    participant DSPAPI as DSP API Server<br/>REST/8888 gRPC/8887
    participant ArgoCtrl as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant TaskPod as Pipeline Task Pod
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata<br/>gRPC/8080
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB<br/>TCP/3306

    User->>Dashboard: Create Pipeline Run
    Dashboard->>DSPAPI: POST /apis/v2beta1/runs (REST/8888)
    DSPAPI->>ArgoCtrl: Create Workflow CR
    ArgoCtrl->>TaskPod: Schedule task pods
    TaskPod->>S3: Store/retrieve artifacts
    TaskPod->>MLMD: Log execution metadata (gRPC/8080)
    MLMD->>MariaDB: Persist metadata (TCP/3306)
    TaskPod-->>ArgoCtrl: Task complete
    ArgoCtrl-->>DSPAPI: Workflow complete
    DSPAPI-->>Dashboard: Run status
    Dashboard-->>User: Pipeline results

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Pattern 4: Notebook Workbench
    participant NotebookPod as Notebook Pod<br/>JupyterLab/8888
    participant OAuthProxy as oauth-proxy<br/>Sidecar
    participant GPU as GPU Device Plugin

    User->>Route: Access notebook URL
    Route->>OAuthProxy: HTTPS Reencrypt
    OAuthProxy->>NotebookPod: Authenticated request (HTTP/8888)
    NotebookPod->>GPU: GPU compute (CUDA/ROCm)
    NotebookPod->>K8sAPI: Submit jobs
    NotebookPod-->>OAuthProxy: Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: Notebook UI

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Pattern 5: Distributed Training
    participant TrainOp as Training Operator
    participant Master as Master Pod
    participant Workers as Worker Pods
    participant Kueue as Kueue Controller

    User->>K8sAPI: Create PyTorchJob CR
    K8sAPI->>Kueue: Admission check
    Kueue->>TrainOp: Admit workload
    TrainOp->>Master: Create master pod
    TrainOp->>Workers: Create worker pods
    Master->>Workers: NCCL/Gloo communication
    Workers->>S3: Checkpoint storage
    Workers-->>Master: Training sync
    Master-->>TrainOp: Job complete
    TrainOp-->>K8sAPI: Update status
